deck: The Smartest Boy in the World
description:
Origin

Bigbrain Billy (no last name ever revealed) lived in the town of Midvale, where he put his high I.Q. to a number of different problems such as designing radio controlled miniature airplanes to find the only man who can save the town from a nearly bursting dam, or helping the local police to outwit criminals. His adventures also took him outside his small town such as the time his science project won a contest and instead of taking the money offered is given a ride to the South Pole to meet Admiral Bird, adventure then ensues.
name: Bigbrain Billy

deck: The Boom Boom Mushroom hides below Neighborville until the Plant team needs its power to defeat the Zombies.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Boom Boom Mushroom

The Boom Boom Mushroom lives secretly in a cave below Neighborville until Crazy Dave and Twister find him. They leave him alone, but later, Dave decides they need his power to combat Zomboss's most recent plan--to drop all of Neighborville below the surface, into some caves.

Dave tells the Patrice and Nate to find the Boom Boom Mushroom so it can blow up the hydraulic elevator that is key to Zomboss's plan. They use Twister, a pig-dog with a sensitive nose, to try to find him.

The Boom Boom Mushroom watches them as they go through the caves but does not announce himself.

Eventually he shows up of his own accord and explodes, defeating a horde of gargantuars. Unhurt, he, Nate, and Boom Boom then run to find the elevator. When they find the elevator, however, Twister rewires it so it brings the zombies to the city surface, where the plants defeat them. The Boom Boom Mushroom seems to continue to stay with them instead of retreating to its subterranean realm.
